          question: "Choose one upcoming test or assignment. Use at least 3 different AI tools to prepare for it. Document your process: Which tools you used, What you asked, What corrections you made, How it affected your preparation. After the test, write whether your scores improved compared to previous tests without AI tools.",
          solution: "Example:\n'Upcoming test: Hindi vocabulary test (20 words)\n\nTools used:\n\n1. ChatGPT — Generated sentences\nPrompt: 'Create a sentence for each of these 20 Hindi words: [list]. Make the sentences simple and funny.'\nResult: Got 20 sentences. Some were funny, some were too complex. I simplified 5 of them.\n\n2. Quizlet — Created flashcards\nUsed the Hindi word as the term, the English meaning + sentence as the definition.\nResult: 20 cards generated. All correct. I added pronunciation hints that AI missed.\n\n3. ChatGPT — Practice quiz\nPrompt: 'Create a fill-in-the-blank test with these 20 Hindi words. Give the English meaning as a hint.'\nResult: 20 questions. Scored 17/20 on first try. Reviewed the 3 I missed.\n\nCorrections made:\n- ChatGPT used a word in the wrong context (formal instead of informal). I fixed it.\n- Quizlet missed the gender of some nouns. I added masculine/feminine labels.\n\nTest result: 19/20. My previous test without AI: 14/20.\nImprovement: +5 marks. The sentence examples helped me remember the words in context, not just their meanings.\n\nLesson: AI tools work best when I combine them — summarize → flashcards → quiz → review. Each tool serves a different purpose in the learning chain.'"
