          solution: "Example:\n'My Brand Sheet:\n\nColours:\n- Primary: Forest Green (#2D6A4F) — represents growth, learning\n- Secondary: Warm Cream (#FAF0E6) — clean, approachable\n- Accent: Terracotta (#E07A5F) — energy, creativity\n\nFonts:\n- Headings: Playfair Display (elegant serif, classic but bold)\n- Body: Source Sans Pro (clean, easy to read)\n\nTagline: 'Curious mind. Creative hands.'\n\nDesign Rules:\n1. Always use cream as background (never white — it's too harsh)\n2. Headings in forest green, body in dark grey (#333)\n3. Use terracotta ONLY for accents (underlines, icons, buttons) — never for large areas\n\nSocial Media Post:\nTopic: 'Why I Love Reading'\n- Background: Warm cream (#FAF0E6)\n- Heading: 'BOOKS CHANGED MY LIFE' in Playfair Display, forest green, 48pt\n- Body: 'Every book I read teaches me something new about the world — and about myself.' in Source Sans Pro, dark grey, 20pt\n- Accent: Terracotta underline below heading (thin line)\n- Visual: An open book icon in terracotta at the bottom\n- Layout: Centered, lots of cream space, clean and elegant\n\nI followed all 3 rules: cream background ✓, forest green headings ✓, terracotta only as accent ✓'"
