          solution: "Example:\n'Old poster (Session 7): 'School Book Club'\n- Used random colours (blue, yellow, red, green — 4 colours, no consistency)\n- Used 3 different fonts\n- Felt chaotic and childish\n- The book icon didn't match the style of the text\n\nNew poster (with brand kit):\n- Used Forest Green + Cream + Terracotta (3 colours, consistent)\n- Used Playfair Display for heading + Source Sans Pro for body (2 fonts)\n- Feels elegant and mature\n- Book icon in terracotta matches the accent colour — everything is connected\n\nComparison:\nThe new version looks 10x more professional. The old version looked like a primary school craft project. The new version looks like something a real bookshop would display. The biggest difference? Restraint. The old version had too many colours and fonts fighting. The new version has a clear hierarchy: cream background is calm, green text is the star, terracotta accents guide the eye.\n\nLesson: Consistency = professionalism. Even a simple design looks polished when everything matches.'"
