          howToUse: "<strong>Step 1:</strong> Go to ted.com/talks.<br><strong>Step 2:</strong> Browse by topic or search for a subject you're interested in.<br><strong>Step 3:</strong> Choose a talk rated 4+ stars (usually the best examples).<br><strong>Step 4:</strong> Watch with a notebook. Note: the hook, the 3 key ideas, body language techniques, and the ending.<br><strong>Step 5:</strong> Re-watch the first 60 seconds. Study how they open. Try to replicate their hook technique in your own presentation.<br><strong>Step 6:</strong> Watch without sound once. Focus only on body language. Notice: hand gestures, movement, eye contact, facial expressions."
