          solution: "Example:\n'Flowchart: 'Should I Post This on Social Media?'\n\n[Start: I want to post something] → [Look at the content] → \n{Is there personal info visible? (address, school, phone)}\n  Yes → [Remove/crop it out] → [Continue]\n  No → [Continue]\n→ {Would I be okay if my principal saw this?}\n  Yes → {Will this hurt anyone's feelings?}\n    Yes → [Don't post it] → [End]\n    No → {Does it add value? (inform, entertain, inspire)}\n      Yes → [Post it] → [End]\n      No → {Do I just want attention?}\n        Yes → [Don't post it] → [End]\n        No → [Post it] → [End]\n  No → [Don't post it] → [End]\n\nDesign: Created in Canva using flowchart shapes. Green for 'post,' red for 'don't post.' Decision diamonds in orange. Actions in blue.\n\nWhat I learned: Making this flowchart revealed that I rarely go through these checks before posting. Most of the time, I just post impulsively. Having a visual decision tree makes me realize there are multiple factors I should consider. I've saved it as my phone wallpaper so I see it before posting.\n\nLesson: Flowcharts aren't just for processes — they're for decisions too. They force you to think through consequences before acting.'"
