          solution: "Example:\n'EXPLORER LEVEL MIND MAP — Sessions 1-24\n\nCenter: 'MY FUTURE SKILLS'\n\nBranch 1 (Green): Digital Skills\n  - Computer basics (CPU, RAM, internet)\n  - AI awareness (types of AI, how it learns)\n  - AI prompting (good prompts, hallucinations)\n  - Digital safety (passwords, privacy)\n  - Digital citizenship (footprint, etiquette)\n  - Smart search (operators, CRAAP test)\n\nBranch 2 (Blue): Creative Skills\n  - Canva basics (templates, fonts, colors)\n  - Poster design (one message, hierarchy)\n  - Advanced Canva (brand kits, layers)\n  - Infographics (data + visuals)\n  - Video creation (plan, shoot, edit)\n  - Creative video (stop motion, time-lapse)\n  - Animation (flipbook, motion graphics)\n  - Audio (recording, editing, podcasts)\n\nBranch 3 (Coral): Communication Skills\n  - Visual storytelling (4 panels, show don't tell)\n  - Presentations (one idea per slide, Rule of 3)\n  - Advanced presentations (storytelling, Q&A)\n  - Confidence (elevator pitch, speak up)\n  - Digital story (full creative workflow)\n\nBranch 4 (Gold): Research Skills\n  - AI learning tools (flashcards, quizzes)\n  - Research with AI (5-step process, verification)\n  - Source evaluation (CRAAP test)\n  - Charts & diagrams (data visualization)\n\nBranch 5 (Purple): Life Skills\n  - Growth mindset\n  - Design thinking (5 stages)\n  - Time management\n  - Collaboration\n  - Problem solving\n\nDesign: Large A2 size (or Canva poster). Each branch has a different color. Sub-branches connected with curved lines. Small icons for each skill. Total: 24 skills mapped.\n\nThis mind map shows how everything connects. Design thinking (Session 23) connects to creative skills AND life skills. AI awareness connects to digital skills AND research. Nothing is isolated — they all feed into each other.'"
