          instruction: "The hero section is the first thing visitors see. Create yours with:\n\n1. Your name (big, bold, readable)\n2. A tagline (5-8 words that describe you or your mission)\n3. A photo of yourself OR an illustration/icon that represents you\n4. A clean background (solid colour or subtle image)\n\nKeep it simple. This section should pass the 3-second test — visitors should know who you are and what your site is about in 3 seconds.",
          example: "Example:\n'My Hero Section:\n\nName: 'ARJUN MEHTA' — Outfit font (same as my Canva brand kit), 48pt, black\nTagline: 'Student. Creator. Future Builder.' — 24pt, grey\nPhoto: A headshot I took against a plain wall (natural light, smiling)\nBackground: White with a subtle light grey section below\n\nLayout: Photo on the left (40% width), name + tagline on the right (60% width). Clean divider line between hero and next section.\n\n3-second test: I showed it to my sister for 3 seconds. She said: 'That's your website. It says your name and that you're a student creator.' Perfect.\n\nTip: Your hero section sets the tone for the entire site. If it's messy, people assume the rest is messy too.'"
