          solution: "Example:\n'My elevator pitch: 'I built a personal website to showcase the projects I've created during my future skills journey. It has my digital stories, infographics, videos, and a bit about who I am and what I'm learning.'\n\nPractice round 1: Too long. Took 15 seconds.\nPractice round 2: Cut it down. 'My website shows the projects I've built — digital stories, infographics, videos. Plus a bit about me and what I'm learning.' Better — 8 seconds.\nPractice round 3: Added energy. 'I built a portfolio website! It showcases my best projects from this course — videos, designs, infographics — and tells visitors who I am and what I'm passionate about.'\nPractice round 4-5: Got it down to natural, conversational tone. About 7 seconds. Sounds like me, not scripted.\n\nFinal pitch: 'I built a portfolio website showcasing my best projects — videos, designs, infographics — and sharing who I am and what I'm learning.'\n\nTip: An elevator pitch should be short enough to say while an elevator rides one floor. If it takes longer, cut it.'"
