          solution: "Example:\n'LINK AUDIT — Arjun's Portfolio V3\n\nInternal Links (within my website):\n1. Home → About | Home page nav | Working ✓\n2. Home → Projects | 'See my work' button | Working ✓\n3. About → Projects | 'Check out my work' link in bio | Working ✓\n4. All pages → Home | Logo click | Working ✓\n\nExternal Links:\n5. Delhi Public School | About page | https://dpspune.edu.in | Working ✓ | Opens in new tab ✓\n6. Canva | Projects page | https://canva.com | Working ✓ | Opens in new tab ✓\n7. CapCut | Projects page | https://capcut.com | Working ✓ | Opens in new tab ✓\n8. The Hobbit | Hobbies page | https://amazon.in/dp/... | Working ✓ | Opens in new tab ✓\n9. Sanjeev Kapoor | Hobbies page | https://youtube.com/@... | Working ✓ | Opens in new tab ✓\n10. Email | Home footer | mailto:arjun@... | Working ✓ | Opens email client ✓\n\nBroken links found: 0 (lucky!)\nAll links open in new tabs: ✓ (except internal nav — those should open in same tab)\n\nTip: Do a link audit before every time you share your website URL. Links can break if websites change their URLs.'"
