          solution: "Example:\n'BEHIND THE WEBSITE\n\nBuilding this website took me 3 sessions and about 4 hours total. Here's what I learned.\n\nThe easy part was choosing the platform. Google Sites was intuitive — it felt like Canva for websites. Adding my hero section and About Me took maybe 30 minutes.\n\nThe hard part was the Projects page. I had to take screenshots, write descriptions, compress images, and arrange everything in a grid. It took me 90 minutes because I kept tweaking the layout. I learned that 'good enough' is better than 'perfect.' My first version was fine — I just needed to stop adjusting.\n\nThe biggest surprise was the QA process. I thought my site was perfect until I tested it on a phone and asked my neighbour to try it. She found 2 issues I'd never have noticed. Fresh eyes are essential.\n\nWhat I learned: Building a website is 30% creation and 70% refinement. The first draft is never the final draft.\n\nIf I did it again, I'd sketch the layout on paper before building. I'd also test on mobile earlier — not at the end.\n\nThis website is mine. I built every section. I'm proud of it.'"
