          example: "Example rehearsal log:\n'ReHEARSAL 1 (Get through it):\nTime: 2:45 (too long)\nStumbled on: The demo section — I kept clicking randomly and lost my place.\nWent well: The hook was strong. I started confidently.\n\nREHEARSAL 2 (Fix content):\nTime: 2:20 (better)\nFixed: Demo section — I now follow a set path: Home → Projects → Video → Hobbies. No random clicking.\nCut: The 'Why' section was too long. Removed one sentence.\n\nREHEARSAL 3 (Delivery):\nTime: 2:05\nWorked on: Eye contact — I looked at my mom instead of the laptop. Used hand gestures when showing the website (pointing at screen). Paused after the hook for effect.\nNeeds work: I still say 'um' when transitioning between sections.\n\nREHEARSAL 4 (Timing):\nTime: 1:58 ✓ (within target)\nCut: 2 seconds from the 'Lesson' section (removed a redundant sentence).\nAdded: A 1-second pause before the closing line for impact.\n\nREHEARSAL 5 (Full performance — recorded):\nTime: 2:00 ✓\nWatched it back: I look confident. The hook lands. The demo is smooth. The closing line has impact. I said 'um' twice — not great, but acceptable for a first presentation.\n\nLesson: 5 rehearsals transformed me from 2:45 of stumbling to 2:00 of confident presenting. The difference is dramatic.'"
