          example: "Example feedback session:\n'Presented to my older cousin (she's in college).\n\nHer feedback:\n1. Hook: 'Yes, the 'three months ago' line made me curious. I wanted to see what you built.'\n2. Demo: 'Easy to follow. I liked that you clicked through pages in order. But when you showed the video, can you play it with sound? I wanted to hear your voiceover.'\n3. Clarity: 'You spoke clearly. Sometimes a bit fast during the demo section — slow down when you're clicking through.'\n4. Natural or rehearsed: 'Felt mostly natural. The hook sounded like something you'd actually say. The middle part felt a tiny bit scripted.'\n5. One thing to improve: 'Make eye contact with the audience, not just the screen. You were looking at the laptop a lot during the demo.'\n\nAdjustments made:\n- I'll play the video with sound on Demo Day\n- I'll slow down during the demo section\n- I'll practice looking at the audience, not the screen (even though I need to click things, I can glance up between clicks)\n\nLesson: Feedback from a real person reveals things you can't see yourself. Every rehearsal with an audience makes you better.'"
