          example: "Example reflection:\n'1. Three things I can do now:\n- Design professional posters, infographics, and presentations in Canva. Six months ago, I didn't know what a template was.\n- Use AI tools for learning — generating quizzes, organising notes, checking facts. I now have a personal AI study toolkit.\n- Build a multi-page website from scratch, including image optimisation, QA, and mobile testing. I never imagined I'd have my own website.\n\n2. Most proud of: My personal portfolio website. It combines everything I've learned — design, writing, project management, QA, presentation. It's the most complex thing I've ever built. Every time I show it to someone, they're impressed that a 12-year-old made it.\n\n3. Biggest challenge: Perfectionism (Session 28). I kept redesigning my website instead of publishing it. I thought it had to be perfect before anyone could see it. My mentor said: 'Done is better than perfect.' I published V1 (ugly), got feedback, and improved it. By V4, it was show-ready. The lesson: you can't improve something that doesn't exist.\n\n4. What surprised me: I surprised myself by enjoying the QA process. I thought testing and checking links would be boring. But I actually liked finding bugs and fixing them. It felt like being a detective. Maybe I'm more detail-oriented than I thought.'"
