          example: "Example:\n'LETTER FROM SESSION 30 (what I wrote then):\n'Dear Future Me: At Session 30, you can design in Canva, use AI for learning, present confidently, manage projects, and have a live website. Most proud of overcoming perfectionism. Hope by Session 40: complete portfolio, multi-page site, Demo Day confidence. Don't forget where you started. Keep building.'\n\nMY RESPONSE AT SESSION 38:\nDear Past Me,\n\nYou'll be happy to know:\n✓ Complete portfolio — done. 5 curated projects with captions on my website.\n✓ Multi-page site — done. 5 pages: Home, About, Projects, Hobbies, Portfolio.\n✓ Demo Day confidence — done. Rehearsed 5 times. Presented in 2:00. Got positive feedback.\n\nWhat surprised me: I enjoyed giving and receiving feedback more than I expected. I also discovered I like the QA process — finding and fixing bugs.\n\nWhat I didn't expect: Building a website was only 30% technical. The other 70% was planning, testing, getting feedback, and improving. That's a life skill, not just a tech skill.\n\nI didn't forget where I started. Session 1 felt like a different person. I'm glad you wrote that letter. It reminded me how far I've come.\n\nKeep building,\nArjun (Session 38)'"
